name: SPECTRUM-INDIA
working_hours: Monday: 10 AM-9 PM, Tuesday: 10 AM-9 PM, Wednesday: 10 AM-9 PM, Thursday: 10 AM-9 PM, Friday: 10 AM-10 PM, Saturday: 10 AM-10 PM, Sunday: 10 AM-9 PM
Review 1: This is a beautiful store. I highly recommend for anyone into spirituality, Buddhism, prayer, crystals, witchcraft, or just curious about Indian, native, or Buddhist culture. This place is a great source of ritual and cultural supplies that may be hard to come-by in their authentic form. They are genuine products, not like you would find on amazon, and are sourced from a small business. They have beautiful jewelry, books, lots of crystals, clothing, incense, and amazing décor. They also offer henna and tarot card readings. They staff is always friendly and happy to help or teach you about their specialties. Always worth a visit, and affordable prices. This is a genuine store that I love!
Review 2: I've been shopping there since I was young now my daughter shopping here and it's still the same place I love it
Review 3: While a bit musky, this niche store is packed with goods ranging from authentic Indian cultural items, to Hinduism, as well as to mysticism. Staff are generally helpful and the prices are OK.
Review 4: Loved the different varieties of sage! Can't wait to try the white sage with dried rose petals. It's gonna smell amazing! Great spot! Glad I came in
Review 5: Spectrum India is a Thayer Street staple! I've been coming here since high school and it truly is a fantastic store. Yes, there are cheaper things on Amazon, but this is the only place where you can chat with Jagdish, while you're picking out your crystals and scarves. My bangle collection is out of this world after almost 20 years of stopping in after dinner at Andreas.
